This paper proposes a deep architecture for multi-label image recognition, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed architecture involves a recurrent memorized-attention module, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions large-scale benchmarks, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses an LSTM sub-network, which is a type of neural network, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
